            . I am a schoolmaster, and live in Great Turner-street, Stepney - the prisoner was <rs id="t18340904-84-deflabel468" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-84-defend545 t18340904-84-deflabel468"></join> to Mrs. Fortman - she supplies me with bread - the prisoner used to bring it - I paid him 3s. 8d. the last bill I paid him, I believe, on the <rs id="t18340904-84-cd469" type="crimeDate">29th of July</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-84-off467 t18340904-84-cd469"></join> - I had paid him money on former occasions.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. DOANE. Q. Have you any receipt? A. Yes - on the bill - sometimes the bill has run two or three weeks.</p>
